  "notes": [
    "Trace has 0 errors — the validation message IS the test's expected outcome, not a failure.",
    "The attachment upload runs on a SEPARATE service/base path (/upload/vnet/...) from the notification app (/notification/vnet/...). 'Add attachment' hands off to it, and that service owns the file-type validation. Architectural split worth noting for the rebuild — the new CDP app should not copy this cross-app hop.",
    "Rejected file: /app/resources/file-upload/example.txt (TXT). Permitted types per the message: DOC, JPEG, PDF, PNG, XLS.",
    "File input is <input type=file id=fileUpload name=fileUpload class=govuk-file-upload>.",
    "Spec title says 'commercial invoice' but the document type actually selected is 'Phytosanitary certificate' (option value phytosanitaryCertificate) — title/behaviour mismatch in the spec itself.",
    "The upload page's continue control is ambiguous in the app — the spec matches it with regex /^(Next|Continue)$/ rather than a fixed label.",
    "Page routes are opaque positional names (consignment/page-1..page-5, documents/page-1) rather than meaningful slugs — a legacy trait the rebuild should not copy.",
    "Commodity search flow is: page-3 (Search Commodities) -> click 'Commodity code search' tab -> page-3?tab=commodity-code-search (enter code + Search) -> POST redirects to page-4?commodity-selected-code=<code> 'Select species of commodity' where the per-species 'Add' button and 'Save and continue' live. Confirmed via per-action input snapshots for actions 19/20 and 28/29.",
    "Action 44 (Inspection premises) logged 'element is not visible' yet still resolved to value INSPBAR1 — the control is conditionally revealed.",
    "Actions 14 (reference number), 57 (contact details) and 58 (nominated contacts) were submitted with NO field entry — defaults/prefill carried them. Those pages' fields are therefore NOT covered by this trace (uncovered surface = finding, not absence of requirement).",
    "Journey never reaches review/declaration/submit — it is cut short by the upload validation, by design.",
    "CAUTION for later waves: this trace zip's network log bundles traffic beyond this test (2493 requests, 7 pages, other drafts). Only the action timeline and its bound snapshots are reliably this test's. This test's draft is 1525765, confirmed via every page's cookie-banner returnUrl. Do NOT derive URLs by reading the request log in order.",
    "No credential-like fill values were present in this trace; nothing required redaction."
  ],
